<h2>How to Measure INP</h2>
<p>INP can only be measured with <strong>field data</strong> from real users. Lab tools cannot produce meaningful INP scores because INP depends on real human interactions. There is no way to simulate which buttons a user will click or how they will interact with your page.</p>
<h3>Where to Check Your INP Score</h3>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Tool</th>
<th>What It Shows</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong><a href="https://pagespeed.web.dev/">Google PageSpeed Insights</a></strong></td>
<td>75th percentile INP from real Chrome users (28-day average)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Google Search Console</strong></td>
<td>Core Web Vitals report with INP status for all pages</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Chrome User Experience Report (CrUX)</strong></td>
<td>Raw field data accessible via BigQuery or CrUX dashboard</td>
</tr>
<tr>
